posts.body:
Monarch Market is Closed for Labor Day.

We’re spending the day resting and recharging with our loved ones and we hope that you are able to do the same! 

We’ll be back tomorrow, ready to serve you during our regular hours.

❤️ Wishing you a Safe and Happy Holiday from all of us at Monarch Market!

Making everyone at the office happy…yeah, that’s tough.

Luckily, at Monarch Market, you don’t have to choose just one restaurant to fit every coworker's craving! From sushi to curry, fried chicken salads to juicy smashed burgers, we’ve got you covered. 

Skip the lunch stress and let us handle it today. Charlotte, your next office lunch just got way easier.

🍤 Lunch goals? Consider them crushed. 🍤

The Tempura Shrimp Bap at Seoul Good is loaded with crispy shrimp, fluffy rice, fresh greens, pineapple, and that Sriracha + Sweet Chili kick that will keep you coming back for more. 🌶🍍

Why settle for boring when lunch can taste this good?

Charlotte, it’s time to upgrade your midday craving! See you at Monarch Market.

☀️ Summer May be Winding Down… but the Tropical Vibes at Lanai Terrace Bar are Still Flowing! 🍹🌴

Sip a craft cocktail, soak up the patio, and let every sip feel like a mini vacation. Because you don’t need a plane ticket to stretch out summer just a little longer. 🌺

OPEN Sun 11-9 | Mon-Thurs 3-9 | Fri 3-10 | Sat 11-10 | Weather Permitting

🍻 It’s almost the weekend… and you know what that means! 🍻

Sunday Pint Night is just TWO days away, and we’re making it a full-day celebration!

Sip on $5 Mich Ultra and Modelo all day long at Monarch Market while catching up with friends and creating Sunday Funday memories.

Tag your crew and make plans—because weekends this good don’t wait.

☕️ The best part of waking up? Kicks Deli breakfast! ☕️

Weekday Grind? Fuel up like a pro with fresh-brewed coffee, overstuffed breakfast burritos, bagels, acai bowls and more. 

🥂 Weekend Mode? Turn it into brunch with mimosas and bloody marys from one of our bars 🥂

Whatever your day’s got in store, Kicks Deli’s got you ready to take it on—one delicious bite at a time.

What’s Better than one Barley & Burger Smashed Burger?

🍔🍔 TWO. Obviously.

Double the patties, double the flavor, and double the reason to treat yourself at Monarch Market.

🔥 Marty McFly – Two smashed beef patties stacked with American cheese, house-made chili, crunchy coleslaw, and mustard on a toasted brioche bun.

🌶️ Ghostbuster – Two smashed patties with pepper jack cheese, jalapeños, and smoky chipotle aioli.

Are you ready for a double feature?

✨ATTENTION: Monarch Market will be Closing at 4PM TODAY, August 6th, for a Private Event. ✨

Planning a celebration of your own? From full buyouts to intimate spaces, Monarch Market offers the perfect backdrop for unforgettable gatherings.

Book:
🌴 The Lanai Terrace – An open-air oasis with elevated tropical ambiance.
🍸 The Aster Cocktail Room – An intimate, moody bar with luxe speakeasy charm.
AND MORE! 

Whether you’re envisioning a chic holiday soirée or a sophisticated corporate affair, our events team will bring your vision to life—seamlessly and spectacularly.

✨ Inquire via the link in bio to begin planning the event of the season!

🌴 Nothing Says Happy Tuesday like Tequila Specials! 🌴

Escape the Uptown rush and slip into the Lanai Terrace Bar — your tropical hideaway at Monarch Market. 

All-day $10 tequila specials featuring Lunazul Tequila, Tommy’s Margarita, and our signature Saddle Up Margarita.

Bold sips. Island vibes. Elevated evenings.
Your agave escape starts now.

☀️🥪 Is it just us… or is a BLT the ultimate summer sandwich? ☀️🥪

Now imagine it with a luxe twist —
Smoky bacon, crisp lettuce, sun-ripened tomatoes… and fresh, flaky SALMON. 

Introducing the Salmon BLT from Off the Hook at Monarch Market — a seasonal favorite, reimagined.

It’s coastal meets classic. Light, elevated, and full of summer flavor. Perfect for a breezy lunch or post work escape from the office grind.

🎣 One bite, and you’ll be hooked. 🎣

reviews_data.review_text: I go to this place almost every day it is so good
No paper towels in the bathrooms and the button to open the door is always broken.  This is annoying for a food hall.

OFF THE HOOK:
We bought a fish taco (cod fish) and the Monday duo. The food was delicious. Shrimp , fries and fish cooked perfectly. Sanitation score 98 in Aug 2025. Service was just ok, but I would still consider returning. His attitude was very  nonchalant. Maybe he was filling in for someone that day, but he knew how to prepare the food, wearing gloves too. That's a plus.
Super Auswahl und alles war lecker.

Nice food court in uptown right across from the Blumenthal theater. Visited with a friend for my first time. Lots of delicious choices. I had the lamb platter from kabobs to go. My friend chose the smashburger from another vendor. We had a nice leisurely slow lunch until it was interrupted by a fire alarm and we had to go outside. Nevertheless we finished outside and eventually came back inside and chatted for a while before we left this place. But a very nice place with multiple selections for food. A very spacious seating area with seating both inside and outside The lobby area. If you're uptown and looking for a quick way to eat that might be a good place to try.
Comimos muy bien a un precio bien también.

Great variety of places to try in here! I tried the monday combo ($17) from off the hook and my boyfriend got the double smash burger ($23 with drink) from the place right next to it. Both tasted amazing and were very flavorful. Only complaint would be the portions being a little small for the price. Definitely would come back and try a new place in here, it was very clean!

If you're in a hurry, do not go to Maroon Market. After waiting 20 minutes (after they said it would be 5 minutes) for our Bao Buns, we went to go check and they said they had run out of buns...After we substituted them for spring rolls, another 10 minutes passed and they were not even started. Then when I requested a refund, it never came! I asked for the manager and they didn't pass ANY information on. I'm wanting my money back still... This was on Monday July 21st, 2025.
sad to see so many good spots come and go due to how hard it is to keep a booth running here. rip foccocina and el veneno
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for sharing your feedback! We appreciate your positive comments about Curry Gate, Kabab2Go, and Barley & Burger. At Monarch Market, we strive to offer a diverse range of culinary experiences with multiple vendors. While we understand that restaurant prices can be comparable, we believe our food hall provides a unique and varied dining atmosphere. We understand your perspective on pricing, and we want to assure you that we continuously strive to provide a diverse and exceptional dining experience at Monarch Market. We'll take your comments into consideration as we work to enhance our offerings. If there's anything specific you'd like to see or if you have additional feedback, feel free to let us know. We appreciate your support and hope to have the opportunity to exceed your expectations in the future.

reviews_data.review_text:
The top spot to go in uptown for food and drinks!
Have a great inside and an outside bar.
And have tonsss of delicious food options for everyone’s tastes!
My honey and I went to enjoy the ambiance. We were not disappointed. We ate at Off the Hook. We ordered the loaded fries with Lobster. Yummy. Fresh and hot.

Love these concepts. Good food and drinks

reviews_data.review_text: Good variety of food types, and all the ones I have tried so far are really good. Plenty of seating.

review_questions.Noise level: Loud, but you can still talk

reviews_data.review_text: Went to Just Chicken. The tenders are sooooo good, the breading is stuck to the chicken and so crispy and flavorful and not greasy or weird like some other chicken places tend to be. The Just Sauce is amazing. My friend tried the Rocky Balboa from the burger place, and she said it was good but greasy. My other friend got Seoul Good and got a Kdog, pot stickers, and jappchae. She enjoyed it! It does seem that maybe lunch is the rush? We went for dinner last night and it was occupied but not ridiculous. I can’t speak to weekends. As the other reviews have pointed out, the fees are wild but if you critically think about it for a second, it makes sense. These businesses have to pay operating and booth fees. So set your expectations and check it out!

The selection of food was nice, of course the overall cost is on par with most of the Uptown restaurants. The atmosphere was also nice. We were there for a coworker's birthday during the week at lunch time and that was the mistake....

The parking IS EXPENSIVE. We parked at 101 N. Church - the website had the wrong address listed for parking- and because it was during the work day (a Tuesday), we paid $13 for an hour and 9 minutes!!! It was about the price of a lunch entre. We even called to make sure that was correct (to the LAZ parking helper) because we were told that Monarch Market DOES NOT VALIDATE PARKING AT ALL DURING THE DAY ON TUESDAY, WEDNESDAY, THURSDAY, OR FRIDAY! Needless to say, we will not be back as a group.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Melissa! We are so sorry to hear that you had a bad experience with our parking validation system. We have $1 parking for up to two hours on weekdays after 4pm, and up to two hours at any point on the weekend with a validation sticker. Our Monday parking is $8 all day with a validation sticker. You are able to pick up a validation sticker at our concierge desk. We hope that you will give us another chance!

reviews_data.review_text: Absolutely beautiful new food market with multiple restaurants under one roof. Great place to unwind with friends or solo. However be warned, food definitely isn’t cheap but guess that’s the way of the world we’re in now. I tried the burger place and for burger/fries and NO drink came up to $25 because everything sold separately. I looked at the menu for the seafood place in there and a lobster roll was abt $28 I believe with no side. So for sure come prepared to spend some money no matter where you chose to eat. I went early on a Saturday morning before a show at Belk Theater so wasn’t a crowd at all which I loved but I can imagine it can get packed later it gets especially on the wkend. I did try the open air bar too right out front which is really nice on a beautiful day to enjoy a beverage while people watching the street.

reviews_data.review_text: The restaurants in here are amazing. The only problem is the building the monarch building charges extra tax on all the restaurants the restaurants do not charge the tax the building does and the restaurant gets none of the money plus they have to pay a extra 6% outta their earnings which is unfair and not right but overall it’s nice just don’t be surprised by all the tax added it’s not the restaurant it’s the building
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you for your feedback and for supporting the amazing restaurants in our food hall. We’re glad to hear you enjoyed the variety and quality of the food!

We understand your concern about the additional service fee. To clarify, this fee is not a tax, but a service charge implemented by the food hall to help cover shared operational expenses that benefit all vendors—such as seating areas, maintenance, cleaning, security, utilities, and other guest services. These services help ensure a clean, safe, and welcoming environment for everyone who visits.

The fee supports the overall experience of dining at the food hall, and we strive to keep it as minimal as possible while maintaining high standards. We appreciate your understanding and continued support of the local restaurants that call our space home!

reviews_data.review_text: This place is overrated. Tiktok lies. The burgers aren't even close to 5 stars. The bar was good. It's not at all worth it.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello! Thank you so much for your rating. We would love to hear more about your visit. Please reach out to us at monarchmarket@hosphq.com. We hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Looks fancy, fast service and very good food.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the kind words! We’re so glad you had a great time and enjoyed the vibe. Looking forward to seeing you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: This food hall has a good variety of options, you can definitely find something for everyone here from sandwiches to sushi and burgers plus more. Two bars are very nice, one inside and one outside, definitely make it seem more high end and add a good vibe to the market. On a very busy day I could see seating being an issue but we were there on a Friday around 8pm and had no trouble. This is definitely a good more reasonable option for the area as it is surrounded by more high end restaurants. We had bulgogi beef bowl from Seoul food and orange chicken bowl from another Asian vendor, both were good. We will definitely return to try some of the other offerings when uptown.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for the great review! We’re glad you enjoyed the variety, the vibe, and had a smooth experience—even on a busy night. Can’t wait to have you back to try more spots next time you’re uptown!

reviews_data.review_text: This culinary collective offers something for everyone in your party, even those with picky tastes (read 4year old.) It’s vibrant, reasonably priced, and the location couldn’t be better. Definitely give it a try before a game, match, concert or show!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Brittany! New offerings coming soon!

reviews_data.review_text: The food quality is mediocre and not worth the price. Service sucks too! LOOK AT YOUR RECEIPT PEOPLE! Monarch Market is ripping customers off red handed. There are 4 different taxes and a service fee on the receipt. The cashier could not explain all of the EXTRA TAXES AND FEES. The only place that has the audacity to blatantly steal from their customers is Monarch Market. My receipts from other restaurants in the area charge an appropriate single NC tax. DON'T WASTE YOUR TIME OR MONEY!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Linda, 

Thank you for sharing your feedback. Our system automatically breaks down the NC state & county taxes into four different categories- while most establishments couple these together into a single tax line. We’re sorry to hear you felt the additional service fee wasn’t clear. The purpose of this fee is to help fund the general upkeep and maintenance of our large storefront in a prime location, ensuring we can continue providing a comfortable experience for all our guests. We understand your perspective and appreciate your feedback as we always aim to improve. We hope you'll consider giving us another chance in the future!

reviews_data.review_text: Great indoor food hall in downtown NC. There was a great variety of selections.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for your review! Stay tuned, always exciting things on the horizon at Monarch Market!

To better understand what happened and ensure this doesn't happen again, could you please contact us at monarchmarket@hosphq.com with more details, including the time of day you visited? reviews_data.review_text: Morgan was our server and we had the best Tommy and Helen margaritas ever! Thank you Morgan and you will see us again soon!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your review! We are thrilled to hear you had such a positive experience with Morgan and we look forward to serving you in the future!

reviews_data.review_text:
Our first lunch visit. We walked the options and settled on Barley and Burger. The wait time from joining the line, ordering, and getting the food was decent but keep in mind it was a Friday holiday. I got the Truffle Shuffle and fried pickles.Yum! As others have rightly pointed out, come prepared to pay above average prices and how much you get to enjoy the environment may depend on when you make the trek. I think it will be worth the occasional walk for us.

*Another visit. Kuya Omakase and their rainbow roll. We've learned to order online and pick it up at the concierge.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your thoughtful and detailed review! We’re so glad you enjoyed the Truffle Shuffle and fried pickles. We appreciate you sharing your experience, and we’re thrilled to hear it was worth the walk! We look forward to welcoming you back soon for another great visit.

reviews_data.review_text: It’s a good spot to grab lunch at work since you and your coworkers can split up to order and then meet up to eat. Love the variety of options, but all of the food is just okay. I’ve been a couple of times, and have not had anything beyond mediocre.

I understand everyone wants to go home, but please stop closing establishments before closing time… I went up to one 30 minutes before closing to a particular restaurant and they were cleaning and told me they weren’t serving anymore. It’s very annoying! Also, lower the prices!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you for your feedback. We understand how frustrating it can be when a restaurant closes early, and we want to assure you that we require all of our vendors to remain open and serve guests until their official closing time. We take such concerns seriously, and we would like to investigate this particular situation further. Could you please provide more details about the specific restaurant in question so we can look into it? You can reach us directly at monarchmarket@hosphq.com. We value your input and appreciate you bringing this to our attention.

Regarding pricing, we are constantly reviewing our offerings and will take your suggestion into consideration as we continue to evaluate our vendors.

Thank you again for sharing your experience with us. We hope to have the opportunity to serve you better in the future.

reviews_data.review_text:
Monarch is nice inside but the "small fee" is 4.5% of what you are purchasing. Not worth it when there are plenty of other restaurants and bars to frequent in uptown. For definition, small is not half of the tax charged already on my purchase. It's maybe 1-2%.
So paying for your rent. Additionally, they don't validate parking so on top of your 4.5%, you get the privilege of paying for that too. I will not be back. I have also spread the word to other coworkers so they know "small" is not truly small.

Lauren,

Thank you for sharing your feedback. We’re sorry to hear you felt the additional fee wasn’t clear. The purpose of this fee is to help fund the general upkeep and maintenance of our large storefront in a prime location, ensuring we can continue providing a comfortable experience for all our guests. We understand your perspective and appreciate your feedback as we always aim to improve. We hope you'll consider giving us another chance in the future!

reviews_data.review_text: Un lugar super recomendable.  Muchas y buenas opciones gastronómicas sin necesidad de gastar demasiado. Muy buen ambiente

reviews_data.review_text: Came into MM at 8:38 and all of the vendors were gone…. Even though the signs say they close at 9pm.

reviews_data.review_text:
Great for groups! I work down the street, and this newer Uptown food hall has always been a crowd pleaser. There are about 10 restaurants and 2-3 bars with a wide variety of options - so far,  they have all been great and made fresh to order. From sushi to smash-burgers to sandwiches and salads, all done very well. Plenty of seating for groups.

Take-out ordering is easy through their website.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your review! We're thrilled to hear that you and your group enjoy the variety of options we offer here at the food hall. It's great to know that everything has been a hit! We truly appreciate your support. Stay tuned for some exciting new offerings coming soon – we can't wait to share them with you! Thanks again for your kind words, and we look forward to welcoming you back soon!

reviews_data.review_text: El Veneno is the best spot in Monarch Market by far. Almost every spot is good but El Veneno is next level.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Brittany! We are thrilled to hear that you enjoyed El Veneno! They have made a fantastic addition to the hall.

reviews_data.review_text: Beautiful just Beautiful.....will be back. There's a restaurant in there that serves "Lobster" rolls and that was dangerous good.

reviews_data.review_text: Great place for lunch or dinner.  Grab a drink at the outside bar in a relaxed atmosphere.

reviews_data.review_text: Falafel Plate from Monarch Market, look how good it looks and sounds on the website order menu. So, I get my food, and it has zero of the delicious “served with” items listed. No hummus, no salad, no pickles, no tahini sauce, no pita bread just DRY falafel patties. I go back to question this, the server says all the served with items are add-ons, extra charge. I show her the menu and she said they have that listed wrong on the website.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi K K! We are so sorry to hear that you did not enjoy your experience at Monarch Market. Please reach out to us at monarchmarket@hosphq.com so we can help rectify this situation. Thank you so much!

reviews_data.review_text:
I love a food hall especially when it's in the heart of uptown and right across the street from Blumenthal.  My wife and I frequently attend shows at Blumenthal and often times try to tie in a dinner or drinks before the show.  I prefer to find something within walking distance which there are several options but Monarch has just expanded those options exponentially.

Our first trip to Monarch was towards the end of summer/ early fall where the outdoor bar was still open. We unknowingly saw the open bar from across the street and decided to grab a few drinks.  It was then that we realized there are several food options.  We had just eaten so we settle on a couple of drinks with the promise that we would return to try the food.  The bar was great as the servers were quick and the drinks were good.  We didn't have any custom cocktails so not much to rate other than they had a great selection.  They have custom cocktails available but we didn't get any.

On our second visit to Monarch we planned to eat dinner and take advantage of the many options.  I landed on Maroon Market which I was quickly disappointed.  I tried to order several things and everything i tried to order they were out of.  This was very frustrating but I'll give them another shot on my next visit and hopefully they will be better stocked.

Since I couldn't get what I wanted at Maroon Market I slide a couple of spots down to Seoul Good which was a great experience.  The lady service was super nice and helpful.  We ordered one of their custom corndogs (half cheese half corn dog) which was an interesting concept.  They have additional options of breading that range from panko to crumbled hot cheetos (or something similar).  These were actually much better than I expected.  I also ordered the tofu rice bowl.  I wasn't a fan of how the tofu was cooked but overall it was a delicious meal and very filling.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your thoughtful review! We're thrilled to hear that Monarch’s location and atmosphere made for a great pre-show experience. We're sorry to hear about your disappointment with Maroon Market's stock, but we're happy to hear you had a great experience at Seoul Good! Your feedback on the tofu is appreciated, and we hope to see you again soon to explore more of our food offerings. Thanks again for visiting, and we look forward to your next trip!

reviews_data.review_text: Food was decent. We had the tandoori chicken.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your feedback! We're glad to hear you enjoyed the tandoori chicken. We hope to have the chance to serve you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: good place

reviews_data.review_text: Loved coming by Monarch Market on my trip to Charlotte, I’ll definitely be back! A huge variety of food is available and you can take it to sit and eat at any of their bars. My bartender, Danny was super knowledgeable and even made me a specialty cocktail based on my tastes.

reviews_data.review_text: Cute place and great meet up spot after work. Aesthetically pleasing and bright. A lot of food choices. It’s our go to stop when going to a concert at spectrum because there’s something for everyone! Food quality at certain vendors are hit and miss is my only warning. It can also be a little pricey but what isn’t in Uptown? The bar has great fresh cocktails, but won’t lie 2 margaritas for $50 bucks is a little wild!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Jackie! We are so thrilled to hear that you enjoy our variety of food options! Thank you so much for your review, we hope to welcome you back soon!

reviews_data.review_text: This is a lovely location with a great environment. The staff here is very nice and understanding with you and the food is top tier.I would recommend this place to anyone looking to try something new in uptown.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Madison! We are thrilled to hear that you enjoyed our food and environment. We pride ourselves on having great staff, as well as a wide selection of food and beverage. Thank you so much for your kind words, we hope to welcome you back soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I loved the food and all of the drink options
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Melissa! We are so glad to hear that you enjoy our wide selection of food and drink options. We hope to see you back soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Great environment, service and drinks are always good.

Such disregard for basic professionalism and the law is utterly unacceptable. I urge management to address this issue immediately to ensure the safety and well-being of their patrons. I will not be returning to Aster until I am confident that appropriate measures have been taken to rectify this alarming situation.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello Abraham. We appreciate you taking the time to communicate your experience. What you have witnessed is a violation of our company standards, which is communicated to all employees in our employee handbook as well as verbally during employee orientation. Any violation of this nature will not be tolerated and results in immediate termination. We are currently investigating this matter and we do have a large number of security cameras within the space so we can deal with this issue expeditiously. If you don't mind, I'd like to get some small details from you. Can you please text me when you have a moment to exchange a couple of texts My cell # is 646-467-3900. Thank you. - Michael

reviews_data.review_text: Outstanding mixologists!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're happy to hear that you enjoyed the expertise of our mixologists! Can't wait to see you again at Monarch Market!

reviews_data.review_text: Purchased the Taquitos and bottle of soda.  $15.16.  They also gave me a bag of chips/quesos which I did not order, but they did charge me.  Food was bland.  Also, the checkout software suggests a tip of 18% + or a custom tip.  Will not be back.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Rosanne, we appreciate your feedback and apologize for the disappointment you experienced during your recent visit. We regret any confusion regarding the chips and queso, and its charge, and we will address this matter internally to prevent future occurrences. Your comments about the food's flavor and the checkout software are noted, and we will strive to improve in these areas to enhance our overall service. We value your input and hope you'll consider giving us another chance to provide you with a more enjoyable dining experience. If you'd like to discuss your concerns further, please feel free to contact us directly at monarchmarket@hosphq.com. Thank you for bringing these issues to our attention.

reviews_data.review_text: Great market with a variety of restaurants that uptown Charlotte was missing.  From 12 to 1 p.m., the place was packed.  So I highly recommend you go earlier or later to grab lunch. Otherwise, you stuck there for half an hour.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your feedback! We're happy to hear that you enjoyed the variety of restaurants at Monarch Market.

reviews_data.review_text: Great news place for lunch. Energetic vibe and good food.

review_questions.Parking options: Paid street parking, Paid parking garage

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the glowing review! We're pleased to offer discounted parking in the One Independence Garage on weeknights and weekends, ensuring a convenient visit next time.

reviews_data.review_text: Very cute!  Different food options so its not all the same.  We went on a cold day and can not wait for the warmer weather to enjoy the outdoor space!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're glad you enjoyed the variety of food options and ambiance! Can't wait to see you again when the weather warms up for some cocktails on the Lanai!

reviews_data.review_text: Awesome food hall in Uptown. My friends and I tried a bunch of the food stalls and they were all impressive and the food was great. The variety of having a couple bars is nice as well. Shoutouts to Curry Gate, Brooklyn Dumpling Shop, Dock Local, Focaccina and Kabab2go. The sandwiches at Focaccina were incredible, the CT lobster roll at Dock Local was delicious and the others we tried were on point. Can't wait to go again.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're happy to hear you and your friends enjoyed Monarch Market! Thanks for shouting out Curry Gate, Brooklyn Dumpling Shop, Dock Local, Focaccina, and Kabab2go. Looking forward to your next visit!

reviews_data.review_text: Just opened, nice variety of food, we will be back!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Glad you enjoyed our new spot and the food variety! We can't wait to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Love the many options. Very unique places here
reviews_data.owner_answer: Glad you enjoyed the variety! We strive to offer unique options. Thank you!

reviews_data.review_text: We visited Monarch Market this past weekend and wow! This is such a cool place with an indoor and outdoor bar, room for outdoor seating and excellent margaritas. Can’t wait for summer and slurp on a drink after work. We walked around and see all the different food stall and noticed the high prices. I understand the cost of food went up, however it won’t be a good 9-5 option from Monday through Friday. $20 for a weekday lunch is not sustainable. However we had curry gate, and it was just as good as the original curry gate and the price was very reasonable. My Palak Paneer with jasmine rice was $12. It will definitely a go to place for a drink and once in a while for a special lunch.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're happy to hear you enjoyed your visit to Monarch Market! Our indoor and outdoor bars offer a cool vibe, and we're glad you loved the margaritas. We appreciate your feedback regarding the food prices, and we're glad you found Curry Gate to offer reasonable pricing and delicious food. We look forward to welcoming you back for drinks and lunch!

reviews_data.review_text: Such good food, great atmosphere and service!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're happy to hear you had such a positive experience with our food, atmosphere, and service! Thank you for your kind words, and we look forward to welcoming you back again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Nice collection of spots. I had Indian, but there were many options available.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're glad you enjoyed our diverse selection of eateries! With numerous options available, we aim to cater to every taste. Thank you for stopping by, and we hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
The place is right off of Tyron street and across from bluementhal ..

The bar has limited options and rather pricey.. for a 5 oz wine (most wines), it was $15 .. 5 oz wine is like taste testing

Too expensive for my taste

The food and vibe was nice.. wish they had more options though..
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Shital, thank you for taking the time to share your feedback. We appreciate your insights and are pleased to hear you enjoyed the food and ambiance. We understand your concerns regarding the pricing and limited options at the bar. We continually strive to provide a diverse and reasonably priced selection for our patrons, and your input is invaluable. reviews_data.review_text: Food at the Burger place was good and juicey. People were very friendly.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're so happy to hear you enjoyed the food at Barley & Burger! Our team strives to provide delicious food, along with friendly service. Thank you for your kind words, and we hope to serve you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Overall, the experience is pleasant. A great hangout place.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're happy to hear you had a pleasant experience at Monarch Market! Creating a great hangout spot is what we aim for, and we're glad you enjoyed it. Thank you for your feedback, and we look forward to seeing you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
Loved stopping by this market to try the restaurants. Curry gate was a 10/10 experience. The food was so flavorful and the customer service was amazing. They are so lucky to have Monica. Her sweet nature will make all the clients want to return.

We tried Seoul for the k dogs and they were also fantastic! We can’t wait to come back :)
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're glad to hear you loved your experience at Monarch Market and enjoyed the flavorful offerings from Curry Gate and Seoul Good! It's wonderful to know that Monica's exceptional service made your visit memorable. We appreciate your kind words and can't wait to welcome you back for more!

reviews_data.review_text:
It is an upscale food court. There are multiple international offerings but from the 3 our group chose it wasn't anything special. None of us got drinks and it was still around $18 each. The location is noisy and crowded. It is hard to see where the lines are vs where people are waiting for food. The trash cans are hidden and not easy to find.

For the price I can got to half a dozen restaurants around and sit down and get served without the hustle and bustle involved here.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for sharing your experience. We value your feedback and apologize for falling short of your expectations at Monarch Market. We hope for the opportunity to better serve you in the future.

reviews_data.review_text:
This is an awesome place to eat,  no to expensive, quick, and delicious 😋
Right at Downtown Charlotte.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're happy to hear you enjoyed your dining experience with us! Providing quick, delicious meals at an affordable price is what we aim for, and we're glad we hit the mark for you. Thank you for your kind words, and we hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: It is ok. Not worth going to unless you are already in town. Optimist and Camp Northend are better food halls.  It is kind of like a nicer corporate cafeteria. But nice happy hour bar to hang. If you are a banker taking a break from doing banker stuff it is good.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Press, thanks for sharing your thoughts. We're pleased to hear you enjoyed the happy hour at our bar. We apologize if our food hall didn't quite meet your expectations, and we appreciate your feedback. Your insights are valuable as we continually strive to enhance our offerings. If you find yourself back in Uptown, we'd love another opportunity to make a better impression and show you the improvements we're making.

reviews_data.review_text: Nice, clean place with 8-10 food vendors. There is a bar in the middle and also outside in the front on the covered patio entry way. Our food was good, service was friendly and the bathrooms were clean.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're pleased to hear you enjoyed your visit to Monarch Market! Maintaining a clean and welcoming environment is a priority for us, and we're glad you found our venue up to standard. We're happy you enjoyed the food, friendly service, and clean facilities. Regarding kid-friendliness, we appreciate your feedback. Just Chicken opened and has a kid-friendly option. We hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Happy Saturday! So, I didn't eat anything prior to leaving for work today.  I went over to Monarch Market. They have a beautiful layout from outside to inside. They have mini good stations set up as to how you would see it inside of a mall at food court.  I walked around to each station as I was undecided on what I had a taste for, but I knew I wanted something delicious to eat. I chose, "Rolled AF." Interesting name, right? I ordered a "Birria crunchwrap." As, of course, it comes with the dipping sauce. When I tell  you, everything was amazing from the layers to the seasoning & perfectly sealed. It's so neatly stacked and fulfilling. I only ate 1/2 of the wrap. You can choose your choice of protein. It's not included.  I paid almost $17, but it's so worth it. It's a beautiful atmosphere for date nights or a girls /guys night out type of vibe.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for sharing your Saturday adventure at Monarch Market! Your detailed explanation of our layout and review of the Rolled AF birria crunchwrap make us glad to hear about your positive experience. We can't wait to welcome you back for more delicious meals with us!

reviews_data.review_text: Ehhh it's okay. Tried the shawarma place, the wrap tasted off, who puts pickles in a shawarma wrap? Fries were soggy even though I asked for them on the side not in the wrap...service was slow despite not being busy at all and having and abundance of staff. Overall, strange experience...there are other, better food halls in Charlotte, this one needs some work.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback with us. We're sorry to hear that your experience fell short of expectations. We appreciate your insights on the shawarma wrap and the fries, and we'll certainly address these concerns with our kitchen team for improvement. Our goal is to provide a memorable dining experience, and we apologize for any inconvenience you faced with the service.

We understand your sentiments and hope you might consider giving us another chance to exceed your expectations in the future. If there's anything specific you'd like to share or discuss further, please feel free to reach out to us directly. Thank you again for sharing your thoughts!

-Monarch Market Management

Great food and great drinks, you can meet with friends, family, and even hold a business meeting here. Working uptown has totally changed for me and my team!
Food is really expensive. Limited options to choose from, but overall it has potential.

reviews_data.review_text:
Great to have another casual dining option in Uptown that's open for dinner! Wish they had online or kiosk ordering like other modern food courts so you didn't have to wait in line (some longer than others--perhaps due to inefficient order intake and not necessarily popularity) and then hope to find a table! They all use the same point of sale (receipts all say "Monarch Market"), so that shouldn't be hard.

The address listed on the website for the parking garage seems incorrect, but we ended up finding a spot on the street anyway.

Yes, some places seem pricey to make a full meal.  The $13.50 chick bap from Seoul Good was ok if you're not super hungry. Might need to add a Korean hot dog, which would be another $7. The focaccia sandwich I got from the Italian street food place was $12 and were a decent size. I just wish it had been hot, not room temp. The best value seemed to be the $10 Nam Khap (called a lettuce wrap, but basically fried rice ok top of lettuce in a prepackaged container) from the Laotion place.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for sharing your experience and valuable feedback with us. Your suggestion about online ordering is noted, and we're pleased to inform you that we now have online ordering available through our website, aiming to provide a more efficient experience. We apologize for any confusion regarding the parking garage address. While the website address is accurate, we're aware of discrepancies with Google Maps, and we've reported this to Google to rectify the issue. Your insights on the pricing and portion sizes are appreciated, and we'll consider them as we continue refining our offerings. We're glad you enjoyed the value of the Nam Khao from Pha Khao and hope to have the opportunity to provide an even better dining experience in the future. Thank you for choosing Monarch Market and for becoming a valued member of our community. Your thoughts are greatly appreciated!

reviews_data.review_text: This place is a whole vibe! Loved the bars.  The food is meh… more food court less food experience but it works. The ambiance is great. We enjoyed our visit and will go again.

Still some things they need to work out: Long lines to order(should have ipad stations at entrance to order at all food stalls to minimize lines at counter) and where to put trash.  Dumpling place wasn't open.  Barley and Burger has great smashed burger with prices comparable to other restaurants uptown.  The two bars are nice touches.  Will try the other restaurants soon.
Love the variety and great layout. Good spot to grab lunch or a drink for happy hour!

Delicious food and the service is impeccable. However, I noticed that all the drinks containing water or ice smells like “wet dog.” There might be something contaminating the water supply for example the pipes. I overlooked it the first time, but noticed it a second time visiting.

Great new spot to eat, many choices of all kinds of food. All the usual fare..
Oder food and find a place to sit down.
Crazy busy!
I ate at focaccina, it was great!!!

I ordered at Tao cuisine, and the photo speaks for it self, for $13 I didn't expect rice in a bag and 1 sausage...
And it wasn't even good. Sausage was dry! And they tried charging me $1 for the smallest amount of sauce.
Other food at this location is better, stay away from this spot
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Nick, apologies for your disappointing experience at Monarch Market. We regret the quality and presentation issues you encountered. Your feedback is crucial, and we're addressing this with our team. We appreciate your honesty and hope you'll reconsider, giving us another chance to deliver a more satisfying dining experience. If you have further suggestions, please contact us directly at monarchmarket@hosphq.com. Your satisfaction matters.

I love love this place. The food options are amazing. I ate at Smashburger and it was perfection b

reviews_data.review_text: I go to this place almost every day it is so good
No paper towels in the bathrooms and the button to open the door is always broken.  This is annoying for a food hall.

OFF THE HOOK:
We bought a fish taco (cod fish) and the Monday duo. The food was delicious. Shrimp , fries and fish cooked perfectly. Sanitation score 98 in Aug 2025. Service was just ok, but I would still consider returning. His attitude was very  nonchalant. Maybe he was filling in for someone that day, but he knew how to prepare the food, wearing gloves too. That's a plus.
Super Auswahl und alles war lecker.

Nice food court in uptown right across from the Blumenthal theater. Visited with a friend for my first time. Lots of delicious choices. I had the lamb platter from kabobs to go. My friend chose the smashburger from another vendor. We had a nice leisurely slow lunch until it was interrupted by a fire alarm and we had to go outside. Nevertheless we finished outside and eventually came back inside and chatted for a while before we left this place. But a very nice place with multiple selections for food. A very spacious seating area with seating both inside and outside The lobby area. If you're uptown and looking for a quick way to eat that might be a good place to try.
Comimos muy bien a un precio bien también.

Great variety of places to try in here! I tried the monday combo ($17) from off the hook and my boyfriend got the double smash burger ($23 with drink) from the place right next to it. Both tasted amazing and were very flavorful. Only complaint would be the portions being a little small for the price. Definitely would come back and try a new place in here, it was very clean!

If you're in a hurry, do not go to Maroon Market. After waiting 20 minutes (after they said it would be 5 minutes) for our Bao Buns, we went to go check and they said they had run out of buns...After we substituted them for spring rolls, another 10 minutes passed and they were not even started. Then when I requested a refund, it never came! I asked for the manager and they didn't pass ANY information on. I'm wanting my money back still... This was on Monday July 21st, 2025.
sad to see so many good spots come and go due to how hard it is to keep a booth running here. rip foccocina and el veneno
